title.74: Sgt. Fury and His Howling Commandos Annual (1965) #6

description.1: Arkon kidnaps the Black Knight because Scarlet Witch just wasn't enough. But now, Arkon isn't working alone; enter his royal consort, the Enchantress!
description.2: Say, "hello," to M.O.D.O.K.'S little friend, Bulldozer Man! Rogers and Wilson find themselves going up against M.O.D.O.K.'S latest invention, tearing through the streets of Harlem. Can Captain America and Falcon stop him before there's nothing left to save?
description.3: The Inhumans must attack the Mandarin to confiscate his rings.
description.5: After a strange, leopard-skinned man is spotted running through the streets, Daredevil pursues! The Man Without Fear meets Tagak the Leopard Lord, and is thrust into a criminal man-hunt from another dimension!
description.6: Once again, Kang strikes from the far future - and this time his weapon is the Hulk himself! With the most unexpected guest-star yet!
description.7: Spymaster prepares his Espionage Elite to destroy Stark Industries. But can Tony Stark and Nick Fury pull a fast one over his head before he completes his mission? Find out when the way-out menace, Spy-Master strikes!
description.9: You'll never forget the monstrous mystery of the World Beyond- or the supernatural Silent One!
description.10: The monster's secret- exposed! Reed's dread decision: who shall die- his wife, or his best friend? A shocker all the way!
description.12: A writer buys an enchanted typewriter that brings his monster stories to life!
description.13: They call her Llyra -- and she commands a sub-sea empire as powerful as Atlantis itself. Bet you'll never guess our shock surprise ending!
description.17: Both Matt Murdock and Daredevil are summoned to court! The judge turns out to be the evil Tribune, and he has filled the court room with his goons! Will Daredevil be able to prevail and serve his own justice?
description.18: The Golem walks among us! And wait till you learn his amazing true identity! A mythical masterpiece that has Hulk up to his ears in trouble.
description.19: Is he human? Can he be killed? Beware the mark of the Mechanoid!
description.21: The Thunder God locked in battle against the powers of Dr. Doom! And, wait'll you read this most unexpected ending!
description.22: Does the Thing become human at last? Is the FF about to break up? And can anything save them from...the monster in the streets?
description.23: The Petrified Man tells of his origins, while Dr. Doom has to battle one of his own, probably to the death.
description.26: It is the funeral of George Stacy and everyone close to the late police captain is in attendance.
description.27: The Wasp visits the Mansion and comes face-to-face with the Liberators, an all-female super hero team fighting "male oppression." Team-leader Valkyrie was a former scientist who exposed herself to a chemical after squaring off with a chauvinistic colleague. Now, Valkyrie is endowed with super-human strength, and will stop at nothing to fight the double-standard of being a super-woman!
description.28: The shocking truth about Bucky Barnes is revealed! Is he here to stay? Or is he merely just a pawn in M.O.D.O.K.'S grand scheme? Will the Sentinel of Liberty finally let go of his old comrade? Find out in this shocking issue!
description.31: Triton! The man called Sting-Ray! The awesome Attuma! Is it a sub-oceanic reunion -- or the greatest battle royale yet?
description.34: New York City is in an uproar of protests! Extremists plant bombs in the hopes of "waking up" America, and Daredevil is caught in the blast radius!
description.35: The Hulk battles the legions of the power-crazed dictator called Draxon. And he's alone in a far-flung clime!
description.36: When the Smashers target Stark Industries, Tony must rocket into action to defeat them before they manage to take his company down. Will the Iron Playboy succeed in eliminating bad business? Find out in Iron Man #31!
description.38: The one you demanded! Dr. Blake, mighty Thor's alter ego, versus the demoniacal and deadly Dr. Doom!
description.39: The battle against Atlantis comes to full blows! The Fantastic Four vs. Magneto- vs. Sub-Mariner! And oh, that ending!
description.41: A vacationing family finds a monster in a swamp!
description.42: Someone close to Peter Parker dies... And he feels responsible.
description.43: The Zodiac holds the entire city of New York ransom for one billion dollars, (1970, folks), and the Avengers must call in back-up. Only two heroes are left to save the day; famed attorney Matt Murdock and Black Panther!
description.44: The Hood decides that the best way to defeat Captain America is through his past. Plotting to use Bucky Barnes lookalike, The Hood plans to kill Captain America. Will the Hood's sinister plan work? Or will Cap come to terms with his past and win?
description.45: The Royal House of Agon vs. the Mandarin!
description.47: Namor -- terrified of the sea that spawned him? You better believe it! Co-starring Captain Marvel.
description.49: While rushing a young boy to the hospital who was attacked by a gang called the Thunderbolts, Daredevil bumps into Black Panther! The two heroes infiltrate the gang and put a stop to their violent acts of crime! A young life hangs in the balance.
description.50: Hydra's back- and they've got ol' Greenskin! But can they hold him? Find out in a most cataclysmic climax!
description.51: While in Japan on a business trip, Tony Stark's world is rocked when the villain, the Monster of Death!
description.53: The Thing battles Namor! Magneto clobbers everyone! And Romita's artwork will flip you out!
description.56: Ka-Zar and Kraven had better hope they don't slip, standing at forty stories high! PLUS Dr. Doom looks for one of his missing Doomsman.
description.57: Spider-Man discovers that Dr. Octopus is not dead!
description.58: After some super-powered sleuthing, the Avengers realize Cornelius Van Lunt's connection to the Zodiac society. With the Scarlet Witch held hostage by the Zodiac, will the Vision switch allegiances to save his love?
description.59: After stopping a student riot, Rogers is asked to make a PSA conference to condemn the students for rioting. When things don't go as planned, The Hood, Baron Strucker in disguise, hires the Batroc's Brigade to take him out. Is this Cap's last speech?
description.61: Namor takes on Hercules -- in the battle of this or any other century! And that's just the beginning!
description.63: Silver Surfer soon realizes that holding back against the Inhumans is not a smart plan. Now, he aims to kill them all!
description.64: Daredevil returns home to NYC to find a brawl waiting for him! The Phoenix, the Fighter, and the Man Without Fear duke it out!
description.65: A titan amidst the tenements! And all that stands between the rampaging Hulk and a helpless Bruce Banner is...Iron Man! This one's a must!
description.66: What trenchant power is infinitely greater than the surging blast from a giant brain? What potent force can bind an entire nation? It is the might that commands the minds of men! Such tyranny Iron Man must challenge if he is to save the people!
description.69: Featuring the sensational Sub-Mariner, and the murderous Magneto! What happens when these two foes align themselves for a war on the surface world? Prepare yourselves...for the eve of destruction!
description.70: Dr. Octopus escapes from prison and decides to take over an airplane! Will Spider-Man get there in time to save everyone?
description.71: A costumed creature named Red Wolf is after a man named Jason Birch. What is Birch's connection to this mysterious being? And how are the Avengers involved?
description.72: Steve Rogers is still enjoying his trip across the country. But things take a turn for the worse when the Red Skull makes a surprise return to exact his revenge! Will Rogers manage to defeat the red menace and avoid an international crisis?
description.73: Witness the epic battle between the Inhumans and the Fantastic Four!
description.75: While in New York City spending time with Diane Arliss, Namor gets involved with a group of youths protesting the destruction of a local park.
description.77: Will the Inhumans be able to survive two deadly missiles launched directly at the Great Refuge?
description.78: Peter Parker finally reveals to his friends that he is Spider-Man.
description.79: Grim Reaper, the leader of the Lethal Legion, plots his next attack against the Avengers. In battle with the Lethal Legion, the Vision discovers that the Grim Reaper is none other than Eric Williams, the ex-con brother of Wonder-Man!
description.80: Taking a break from his never ending battle against villainy, Captain America hits the open-road. But when he's mistaken for a member of the Satan's Angels gang, Captain America finds himself on the other side of crime.
description.81: Bruce Banner agrees to help Mar-Vell escape the Negative Zone, but becomes enraged and turns into the Hulk!
description.82: Karen Page convinces Daredevil to star in her show. Nearby, Stilt-Man disguises himself as the Stunt-Master and lingers by the soundstage looking for action. Before long, Stunt-Master gets the action he's looking for!
description.83: At the end of his rope, Bruce Banner seeks a cure for his gamma radiation...with disastrous results. Now, the Hulk and Banner are two separate entities- with two very different agendas!
description.84: Tony Stark must rocket into action when he receives a distress call from an old flame. The Controller lives! And he has vengeance on his mind!
description.86: The whole team, taken unawares by the Maggia! Will the evil Top Man get ahold of Reed's experiments? The Invisible Girl pulls out all the stops to defend her teammates...and her family!
description.88: A dual story EPIC featuring a battle between Ka-Zar & Kraven the Hunter! Dr. Doom aims to prove his intellectual superiority!
description.90: If Namor dares battle the mysterious Commander Kraken, both Dorma and Diane Arliss may die! And yet — battle he must!
description.93: Brother Brimstone strikes again! This time, the murderer goes after Karen Page! Daredevil races to save his beloved, but the La Brea Tar Pits threaten death.
description.94: Our green-skinned goliath fights for his life against the unstoppable, revenge-crazed Glob! It's the rematch you've been waiting for!
description.95: It's Iron Man against the world! Introducing the Firebrand, the most controversial super villain in the history of comic books!
description.96: Thor vs. The Abomination! And this is one well-matched fight!
description.97: The sensational 100th-anniversary issue! Jam-packed with more super-villains than you can count! The Fantastic Four must withstand the latest foil from the Mad Thinker and Puppet Master. And you'll never guess what these villains have up their sleeves!
description.99: The origin of Black Widow!  Spider-Man goes toe-to-toe with Black Widow as we learn more about her mysterious past.
